					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of kabbalistic works.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="1r" to="40r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sha῾are tsedeḳ</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שערי צדק</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/122229986">Gikatilla, Joseph ben Abraham, 1248-</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/122229986">ג'יקטיליה, יוסף בן אברהם</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>The Latin title: "Portia Justitiae" is written twice on the upper margin.</p>
							</note>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Shaare_orah_1959"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">זה הספר כתבתיו אני <name type="person" role="scribe">יצחק</name> הצעיר מצעירי התלמידים בכמ"ר יעקב צרפתי זלה"ה וכתבתיהו ב<name type="place">אנקונא</name> דהיינו השערי צדק והבהיר וקצת מדרש רות : הקצת האחר והפירוש מהתפלות כתבם לי ר' <name type="person" role="scribe">נתנאל צבע מע' סוברינו</name> שהיה דר באנקונא : אמנם הפירוש המצות שחברם הר' מנחם מריקנטי זלה"ה שחברם של דרך הנסתר גם פי' ברכת המזום
על דרך נסתר כתבתים אני יצחק הנז' בעבורי ובעבור זרעי וכו'.<locus n="133r"/>
							</colophon>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="40r" to="50v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-bahir</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר הבהיר</title>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Bahir_1820"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<note>
								<p>Many corrections supplied in the margin.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="50v" to="71r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Zohar ḥadash (Midrash Rut)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he"> זהר חדש (מדרש רות)</title>
							<filiation>Cf the contents of Add MS 27009, II (<ref target="Margoliouth_1965" type="number">751</ref>).</filiation>
							<note>
								<p>Some notes are given in the margin, including a few in Latin.</p>
							</note>
							<textLang mainLang="tmr"/>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="71r" to="100r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Perush tefilot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">פרוש התפלות</title>
							<note>
								<p>The work stems from Abraham Abulafia's school. See <ref target="Idel_1976" type="page">77</ref> and p. 84 nn. 38 &amp; 39. </p>
								<p>There is a title "Expositio orationum p Cabala."</p>
								<p>Two complete wheels with Hebrew letters and words (for permutations) are placed at the beginning, folio 71r &amp; 72r.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="100r" to="131v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">[Sefer ta῾ame mitsṿot]</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">טעמי המצוות</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/101087390">Recanati, Menahem ben Benjamin, active 13th century-14th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/101087390">רקנטי, מנחם בן בנימין</persName>
							</author>
							<listBibl>
								<bibl>
									<ref target="Mitsvot_Rekanati_1581"/>
								</bibl>
							</listBibl>
							<note>
								<p>A number of passages have been added in the margin, and there are some marginal Latin notes.</p>
								<p>Folios 100r-101r contain an index of the commandments dealt with, the number being 102.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="131v" to="133ר"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Perush birkat ha-mazon</title>
							<title xml:lang="he"> 	פרוש ברכת המזון</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/101087390">Recanati, Menahem ben Benjamin, active 13th century-14th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/101087390">רקנטי, מנחם בן בנימין</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="133r" to="135v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Yiḥud na᾿eh</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ייחוד נאה</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/31723429">Ibn Waqār, Joseph ben Abraham, active 14th century</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/31723429">יוסף בן אברהם אבן וקאר</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment.</support>
								<extent>135 folios<dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
										<height>217</height>
										<width>153</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>170</height>
										<width>115</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>135 folios (+ 4 unfoliated paper flyleaves at the beginning and at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>Quires of mostly 10 leaves each.</p>
								</collation>
								<condition>
									<p>All the leaves too closely cut.</p>
								</condition>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="1 " ruledLines="40" writtenLines="40">
									<p>Uniform layout.</p>
									<p>Complete hard-point ruling visible.</p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable.</p>
									<p>Initial words in sections in larger characters.</p>
									<p>Many additions and comments in the margin.</p>
									<p>Catchwords on every verso (those at the end of quires distinguished by a special mark).</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="2">
							<summary>Italian semi-cursive scripts of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Yitsḥaḳ ben Ya῾aḳov Tsarfati of Ancona</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 133r.</summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="sole">
								<p>
									<locus from="57v" to="101r"/> written by the second scribe, <name type="person" role="scribe">Natan᾿el Tseva῾ of Severino</name>: inscribed in the colophon, folio 133r.</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>Post-1600. Brown leather, with golden tooling.</p>
								<p>Spine: 'Cabbalistic Works. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional 16,407.'</p>
							</binding>
						</bindingDesc>
